            "content": "Fall Protection and Safety Glass Requirements: Arizona building codes mandate specific safety requirements for skylights based on location and installation type. Skylights within 36 inches of walking surfaces (roof decks, elevated platforms) must meet impact resistance standards equivalent to tempered or laminated glass. For homes with children, we recommend laminated glass even when not code-required—if glass is broken by hail or debris impact, laminated construction holds shattered glass in place preventing falls and injury. Ventilation code requirements: Bathroom skylights meeting minimum ventilation requirements (typically 1 square foot of ventilation per 100 square feet of floor area) may eliminate need for separate mechanical exhaust fans—saving installation cost and energy. However, skylights must be operable (venting models) to qualify as code-compliant ventilation. Fixed skylights do not satisfy ventilation code requirements."
