            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "Water stains on ceilings or walls around skylights indicate either active leaks or historical water intrusion. Diagnosis required: We perform comprehensive leak diagnosis using water testing (controlled water application to identify exact entry point), moisture meter scanning to detect hidden moisture in surrounding materials, dye testing for pinpoint leak location when source isn't obvious, and thermal imaging identifying temperature differences indicating moisture presence. Common leak sources: Deteriorated flashing (most common—accounts for 90% of skylight leaks), failed sealant at skylight perimeter, improperly integrated flashing with roofing materials, damaged skylight curb allowing water intrusion, cracked or damaged skylight glass or frame, and ice dam formation in rare hard freezes (very uncommon in Tucson). Professional repair approaches: Reflashing skylight with new ice and water shield and metal flashing components, replacing deteriorated curb components, resealing skylight unit to curb, replacing damaged skylight components or complete unit if necessary, and repairing interior water damage to drywall, insulation, and finishes. Attempting DIY leak repairs with caulk or roof cement rarely succeeds—proper repairs require understanding water flow patterns and comprehensive flashing knowledge. Our leak repair service includes diagnosis ($150-$300), complete repair with warranty, and verification testing ensuring problem is fully resolved."
